/wiki/Ubigeo: Ubigeo is the coding system for geographical locations ( Spanish : Código Ubicacíon Geográfica ) in Peru used by the National Statistics and Computing Institute ( Spanish : Instituto Nacional de Estadística e Informática INEI ) to code the first-level administrative subdivision : regions ( Spanish : regiones , singular : región ) , the second-level administrative subdivision : provinces ( Spanish : provincias , singular : provincia ) and the third-level administrative subdivision : districts ( Spanish : distritos , singular : distrito ) .
/wiki/Ajoyani_District: Ajoyani District is one of ten districts of the province Carabaya in Peru .
/wiki/Ayapata_District: Ayapata District is one of ten districts of the province Carabaya in Peru .
/wiki/Coasa_District: Coasa District is one of ten districts of the Carabaya Province in Peru .
/wiki/Corani_District: Corani ( from Aymara Qurani , meaning the one with herbs ) is one of ten districts of the Carabaya Province in Peru .
/wiki/Crucero_District: Crucero District is one of ten districts of the province Carabaya in Peru .
/wiki/Crucero: Crucero is a village ( Spanish : aldea ) located between Bueno and Pilmaiquén River in Río Bueno commune , southern Chile .
/wiki/Ituata_District: Ituata District is one of ten districts of the Carabaya Province in Peru .
/wiki/Macusani_District: Macusani District is one of ten districts of the Carabaya Province in Peru . Its seat is Macusani .
/wiki/Macusani: Macusani is a town in Southern Peru , capital of the province Carabaya in the region Puno .
/wiki/Ollachea_District: Ollachea District is one of ten districts of the province Carabaya in Peru .
/wiki/Ollachea: Ollachea is a genus of parasitic flies in the family Tachinidae . There is one described species in Ollachea , O. elongata .
/wiki/San_Gaban_District: San Gaban District is one of ten districts of the province Carabaya in Peru .
/wiki/Usicayos_District: Usicayos District is one of ten districts of the Carabaya Province in Peru .
